      "date": "2020-07-19 15:42:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis is just a nasty hack to show it is possible to do BIO as DIO, and let people see that big buffers are usually (I think almost always?) page aligned.\n\nThis is *not* how this will be done for real; it even breaks lfs setstripe.  All you can really do with this is read/write aligned i/o.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
