      "date": "2021-09-08 05:34:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nPatrick, what would be much more interesting here than pushing *all* buffered IO to be DIO, would be doing this dynamically based on IO size, like what is done on the OST with osd-ldiskfs.*.readcache_max_io_mb and ...writethrough_max_io_mb.  \n\nSomething like 1MB and larger IO requests would be suitable for conversion, as a first guess.",
